From: Fox in the Box overlay <noreply@fox-in-the-box.local>
Subject: [PATCH 003/003] Restore Fox onboarding redirect in server.py

The v0.6.0/v0.7.0 (Phase 7/8) overlay migration moved
fox_overlay/webui_modules/onboarding.py + setup.{html,css,js} into the
overlay package, registered the /setup and /api/setup/ dispatcher
routes, and added .fox-removals entries for the old static/onboarding.js.

What it did NOT do: write a patch to re-install the redirect middleware
into virgin upstream's server.py. v0.5.4 had it inline at server.py
lines 147-148 and 167-168. Once the submodule was re-pointed at virgin
upstream in Phase 8, those lines were gone — so every fresh-install user
landing on / went straight to upstream's chat shell instead of being
bounced to /setup for the Fox wizard.

This patch restores the wiring: import Fox's two onboarding helpers
(guarded so vanilla webui without fox_overlay still boots) and call them
at the top of both do_GET and _handle_write (which is shared by
do_POST/do_PATCH/do_DELETE — so this single insertion covers all
write methods, not just POST).

Reference: forks/hermes-webui@62c08548:server.py lines 95, 147-148,
167-168 (the v0.5.4 pre-migration state). Issue #331.

diff --git a/server.py b/server.py
index 65b22077..aeb79339 100644
--- a/server.py
+++ b/server.py
@@ -122,6 +122,20 @@ except ModuleNotFoundError as _fox_e:
 except Exception as _fox_e:
     logger.warning("fox_overlay.bootstrap failed (%s); Fox routes disabled", _fox_e)

+# Fox onboarding redirect: bounce un-onboarded users to /setup before any
+# other routing fires. v0.5.4 had this inline; the Phase 7/8 overlay
+# migration moved the helpers into fox_overlay.webui_modules.onboarding
+# but never patched the wiring back into server.py — every fresh-install
+# user landed on upstream's chat shell instead of the Fox wizard (#331).
+try:
+    from fox_overlay.webui_modules.onboarding import should_redirect_to_setup, redirect_to_setup
+except ModuleNotFoundError as _fox_e:
+    if _fox_e.name != "fox_overlay" and not _fox_e.name.startswith("fox_overlay."):
+        raise
+    should_redirect_to_setup = lambda _path: False  # noqa: E731 — vanilla-webui fallback
+    redirect_to_setup = None
+
+
 _CSP_CONNECT_BASE = (
     "'self' http://127.0.0.1:* http://localhost:* "
     "ws://127.0.0.1:* ws://localhost:*"
@@ -316,6 +330,10 @@ class Handler(BaseHTTPRequestHandler):
             set_request_profile(cookie_profile)
         try:
             parsed = urlparse(self.path)
+            # Fox #331: bounce un-onboarded users to /setup before auth.
+            if should_redirect_to_setup(parsed.path) and redirect_to_setup is not None:
+                return redirect_to_setup(self)
+
             if not check_auth(self, parsed): return
             result = handle_get(self, parsed)
             if result is False:
@@ -339,6 +357,10 @@ class Handler(BaseHTTPRequestHandler):
             set_request_profile(cookie_profile)
         try:
             parsed = urlparse(self.path)
+            # Fox #331: same redirect on POST/PATCH/DELETE (shared method).
+            if should_redirect_to_setup(parsed.path) and redirect_to_setup is not None:
+                return redirect_to_setup(self)
+
